  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "After careful evaluation, we selected the Swin3D model, which has demonstrated state-of-the-art performance across a range of tasks and is particularly well-suited for large-scale video classification tasks like ours 27.",
    "Swin3D is a state-of-the art three-dimensional video classification transformer that has demonstrated state-of-the-art performance for various tasks 27.",
    "Transformers have demonstrated great potential for stenosis assessment in comparison to convolutional networks, and work best using large datasets, which we have access to ref. 2.",
    "Swin3D's classification layer 27 was modified to perform regression by changing the activation function to a Sigmoid function and changing the output size to get one continuous value between 0 and 1, corresponding to a stenosis percentage (Supplementary Video 1 shows an example of Deep-Coro's output).",
    "One hot encoded vector identifying the coronary artery to which the stenosis belong, and a normalized value of the patient's age were concatenated to the last feature vector of the model."
  ],
